                <p>Across the six indicators, most show consistent top matches between Spearman and DTW, indicating that
                    both trend direction and overall pattern align closely with past pre-recession periods. However,
                    <strong>unemployment</strong> and <strong>VIX</strong> diverge, with different top matches under
                    each method, suggesting these
                    indicators are more sensitive to timing shifts and volatility patterns rather than just directional
                    trends. Overall, this highlights that while many indicators follow stable and comparable
                    trajectories, others require time-aligned analysis (DTW) to fully capture their similarity to past
                    cycles.
                </p>



